</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubribrisos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bribrisos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/7/01 8:00:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nagafen Recap</span><hr size=1>  Omg wow. Lag lol surprised me, you put on my face a big big smiles when I saw &quot;and Brisos&quot; but when I saw you talked to me in french the smile did 3 times the turn of my head.<br>
 Anyway everything I said, if yo uremember being so tired, was true. And I will always be ready to meet as well. You still have to meet my girlfriend, she is the best little comforting thing in the world. I hope we bot hwill be able to attend your Vox raid. Cya then ! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utildartreewalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tildar Treewalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/7/01 11:02:04 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.emeraldaxe.com/images/tildar/sigpic_20.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nagafen Recap</span><hr size=1> Well I for one was amazed all night and for the first time in months my blood was pumping and I was really excited about this game, so thanks to the leadership for that.<br>
<br>
I would however like to say I was one of these dinks that did not bind in the antechamber... it was my first raid and I was a bit overwhelmed. I also did not hear anyone say run in and die to gain mana... I saw it after the fact while I was in freeport thinking how dumb it was that I didn't bind.<br>
<br>
I would however like to mention the biggest part of the raid for me personally was the FG Psycho pull... I think it got out of control when the FG wizard cast gravity flux and we all ended up on the celing :) When the clerics started camping I was completely ready to die for the cause, but I was really determined not to let anyone else in my group die. Sinian was so close I didn't see any yellow when I started to heal him ... Whew he lived... not one of my group died... I turned to my friend here at work after the fight and let out a big HOLY $ <p><A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=9288">Tildar Treewalker</A> <BR>
Druid of Tunare <BR>
Emerald Axe <BR>
<A HREF="http://www.emeraldaxe.com/tildar"> Tildar's Druid Pages <BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubribrisos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bribrisos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/8/01 5:52:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nagafen Recap</span><hr size=1>  I think it's a good thing that you psoted here Tildar. That just shows that if peoples didn't bind in antechanber and die to gain mana back it was not, for all of them, cause of their lack of brain.<br>
 Some of them then didn't do it cause no oen told them to do, or not loud enough, or they didn&quot;'tpay attention at this time.<br>
 That jsut means that for next raid everyoen will know it now and at least all of those I talk about, those who did a little mistake, wil ldo it. But the real dumbs who will keep doing what they think being the best well... For Naggy if I remember well we would have needed jsut one or two nukers to go back in and nuke. So I m deeply sure it will work way better next time.<br>
 I wanna thank you Tildar. Thank you. Hehe easy...<br>
 Hum..<br>
 Brisos. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usinian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/8/01 3:59:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nagafen Recap</span><hr size=1>  Well I for one am greatful for Til's, work at keeping me alive. After the fourth time I was summoned in that FG mess I was sure I was about to die. But like a good bard I decided to hide in the corner and shut the hell up so I could be found and healed. Good thing I did, it allowed me to be summoned three more times before we killed that wizard. His efforts on that raid proved to me once more to trust a druid over a cleric when you need a healer.<br>
<br>
 As for the rest of the group, we were a wonderful team. I bet we could've taken on any spawn in Lguk as is. Which brings me to my criticism of the raid, I saw a lot of individual groups. I did not see anything resembling two groups to form a whole. We can chalk this up to people not listening to the raid commanders, to be honest I never knew Lag was a woman, but I'd rather chalk that mark against the leaders themselves.<br>
<br>
 It is true that people will chose their leaders and place faith in those that have proven themselves. So this raid started with that mark against Lag and her inexperience with leading something of this magnitude. We entered this raid with fewer then was expected. I think rather then sticking to the plan layed before us, we should've seen a bit more ingenuitey and restructuring as to the tools we had. The raid was beautifully planned if we had the resources for that plan it would've worked. We had plenty of tanks IMHO to take out naggy. the problem was the healers could not keep up with the wounded and were oom. So what would you have us do but loiter around waiting for them to get mana. It is my expierence that battles are decided by the tanks. The longer they can keep naggy away from the nukes for the final push the better.<br>
 <br>
 We had something on this raid that I know is unheard of, more then 5 bards. With this many bard staying with the few tanks we did have turns the last few into nothing more then fancy meleer's with drums. I think it would've been in the raid's interest to set a bard or two on the tirage line to keep the healers mana happy and thereby keeping the few tanks alive.<br>
<br>
 As for the nukes, well I can not speak for them as I was busy trying to keep my tanks buffed and my healer full. I will say that there didn't seem to be enough of them and they were called in way to early. It could seem that way because some of our nukes were a one time use, if by their own design or by accident. Needless I knew the nukes had been called in too soon when the command was shouted and I held my own nuke till he was at 20%.<br>
<br>
 Another thing I noticed were the commands themselves in the heat of the battle. They were shouted mabey once at a time and were in no format at which you could read them. This lead to a sickening feeling that the leaders had panic'd. Despite this I pushed on. After playing a bard for so long I've really learned to read the way a battle swings and how to play my part as to save as many as possable. I do not believe Lag has fully learned the part of a raid master, and can only pray she learned from her own mistakes she made on this raid. I will be there for Vox, against my better reasoning, mostly to see if the leaders have learned to adapt to what comes their way. To be honest it sickens me that they HAVE NOT accepted any of the failure of this raid on their own part.<br>
<br>
Sinian Songstealer<br>
<br>
&quot;Tis easy to blame others, but do you not find the fault within yourself?&quot;<br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uflarrenlagdalen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flarren Lagdalen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Disciple</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/8/01 6:23:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nagafen Recap</span><hr size=1> Well geez, I'm gonna have to respond to that attack now dont I.<br>
<br>
Paragraph by paragraph - <br>
<br>
The wizard for an extended period was Yurian's pet (a friend of Mine lvl 59 Enchanter) and she had it attacking the other giants. I am assuming you were pounded on by it either in the beginning of the fight or after it was the target. There were 2 healers pretty much in every group and they should have had almost no trouble keeping up with the heal load though yes I did call for clerics to camp as soon as I realized how many were in the room. Some of them blatantly disregarded that order but thankfully most left anyway.<br>
<br>
I can only work with people that are willing to work with others. From my vantage before I died many were using the assist command, though the giants were running around and people were finding it hard to follow 1 target at a time. The idividual groups I felt were strong enough to kill them almost unaided and since Yurian had been debuffing and slowing them I believe that gave eveyone a dicisive advantage. If people dont understand what the /assist Kommisar command meant then what are they doing at high lvl? Were they powerlvled and are now high lvl newbies? If so I dont want them. It's not a criticism against the person, it is the strong belief that they havn't spent enough time learning their char to properly apply themselves and until they get more exp I will not risk my raid with their lack of knowledge.<br>
<br>
I am far from new to running raids, I am simply new to running CoG's raids. MANY of you have seen me at every plane and dragon run done since SB reopened dragon runs and some of you will remember me going on dragon raids before half of you were lvl 20. Why dont I lvl? Because I promised my GL I would get him a white dragon scale for his epic weapon and I'm not going to break my promise. Now granted the people I was hoping to see didn't all show and since CoG has an incredibly large turnover rate we did not have many with dragon exp so THAT is what made our job hardest. I dont know about the rest of you and even Flarren agrees with me, alot of &quot;tank classes&quot; simply cannot keep up like a warrior does in combat. They dont have the life, AC or skills (dual wield etc) to keep up like warriors do, and so warriors make or break the raid. We had 5 warriors. <br>
<br>
Now let me explain to you why it is completely pointless to put a bard on triage line. FIRST of all if a healer is OOM they dont sit on their ass medding, they get in there and die, BOOM fm. And then they start healing again. SECOND If we were to leave a bard on triage there is a max of 2 healers that would benefit and all the xtra dmg that bard could do would be lost. Waste of time, not happening, healers die to get mana or I find healers that will.<br>
<br>
Now for nukers. My strategy was to send them in at 45%, how DARE you defy my command and tell whoever the nuker was to wait. (odd side note - with your group leader being Flarren [my rl husband] and you having Madkat, Aeval, Tildar and Bainzeal in your group who exactly were you telling to wait since you were in a tank group, not a caster group?) Maybe if he/she had been in from the beginning we might have done that extra 1000 dmg and pushed him into run mode. When I call nukers in I mean nukers in NOW. We had lost sufficient tanks by that point that caster deaths instead of tank deaths was an acceptable loss and needed in order to give the tanks time to run for a heal while Naggy was distracted. Everyone gets a rez anyway so there should be no reason to complain.<br>
<br>
I admit yes I should have repeated commands more than I did. Not everyone stops to read the red on their screen and next time I will be spamming the zone so you guys can read it clearly. I had not pannicked and never did. As I stated above I am FAR from being an inexperienced raid commander BUT I am used to working with a crowd that listens for their own good. My orders were never questioned before when I called them, they were simply done so why should they be questioned now? Afterall, whoever it happens to be - your raid leader is your raid leader. No one else. I've been playing since just barely after beta so I'm not exactly stupid as to the ways of battle either and from my standpoint things were going well until suddely everyone stopped with no command called to do so. If you had to force yourself to sign your name onto the Vox list then go take it off. If you have that little faith then you are one of the people I dont need.<br>
<br>
If I hadn't accepted responsibility for what happened would I have been sitting here balling my eyes out while Flarren tried to get things back together from my comp? Would I have been questioning every move I made all night if I didn't realize what could have been done differently? Could I honestly NOT believe it was all my fault? And if I had taken absolutely no responsibility for it as you say, would I have said in shout speech..<br>
<br>
/shout I dont know what to say guys. I am taking full responibility for us failing and I appologize to you all profusely for it going all wrong. I just dunno what to say or how to say sorry to you all enough =(<br>
<br>
*cut from original recap post*<br>
**************************<br>
-I believe I made 2 colossal mistakes (not counting the small ones too) thoughout the raid. In group movements to get inside I didn't take enough time to get my team aquainted with the system I wanted to use. That will be corrected. And mistake number 2 is not as easy to admit but *gulp* in the last final seconds before making our first rush I failed to notice a couple of my group leaders saying they were still missing their healer. Obviously hesitant they stopped (which they shouldn't have done anyway but I understood why they did) and everything back clogged in the first 20 seconds. <br>
<br>
-I cant place into words how sorry I am for not doing these parts better. Especially the Attack command. For this I appologize profusely and beg everyone to remember it was my first time leading a dragon raid and that now I have learned ALOT from what I did wrong.<br>
**************************<br>
<br>
Maybe if you'd had your ears open you would have heard that too. Now you had valid points and you had opinions and I believe I responed to all your suggestions with my reasons why it was, can, can't or wasn't done that way. I feel your post was a direct attack on me at some points and it was NOT called for. If you can do a better job then I welcome you to go try sometime. It is NOT as all fired easy as you think it is.<br>
<br>
Lagdalen Tarcho <br>
lvl 51 Elemenalist Officer<br>
Dragon exp - over 11 kills, talk about fails<br>
<br>
