 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uflarrenlagdalen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flarren Lagdalen</A> at: 5/8/01 7:41:13 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueuwynofkarana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EuwynofKarana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/8/01 10:26:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nagafen Recap</span><hr size=1> Alright, I had this big long thing typed, was signing it, and then I accidentally somehow hit back with my dang mouse, and now I have to retype, so excuse me if I miss anything...Ok, here goes<br>
Wow Sinian, I'm completely shocked at how you made such outrageously wrong claims, and were so cruel to somebody who spent days getting ready to allow you this opportunity, and all you can do is say BS to their face, well I for one will not put up with this!<br>
<br>
#1. &quot;I will be there for Vox, against my better reasoning, mostly to see if the leaders have learned to adapt to what comes their way. To be honest it sickens me that they HAVE NOT accepted any of the failure of this raid on their own part.&quot;<br>
~~Alright, this is a completely unacceptable remark, &quot;against my better reasoning&quot;, thats disrespectful, and I guarantee you its now against the raid leader's &quot;better reasoning&quot; to ever let you on a CoG raid, and anybody from any other guilds who may read this, for this horrible display of feelings. Oh ya, and I guess you know everything about nagafen raids and Lag and Flar don't, and I'm guessing that the FG pull to the throne was common too, and they didn't react well and we didn't kill all of them...alright, now /sarcasm off. Final thing for this reply, they HAVE NOT accepted...yadayadaBS! Have you read any of the posts Lag put? she said that she was sooo upset and blamed herself completely that she couldn't bare to check recap posts for a couple days. We had a couple problems, and many, no, most weren't her fault.<br>
<br>
#2. &quot;...and they were called in way to early...Needless I knew the nukes had been called in too soon when the command was shouted and I held my own nuke till he was at 20%.&quot;<br>
~~ Alright, this is another comment that really disappoints me, you think you know everything don't you? Ya, I'm not running this raid, but I think it would be better if I waited to nuke so the tanks have more time to miraculously hang on for 5 minutes of abuse, and nuking to finish him off faster would only hurt the tanks' chances of staying alive. I mean come on, use common sense, I guess u haven't been on one of these before b/c thats completely LUDICROUS to disregard what the raid leader says, they are law, and u a peasent of the 1200s (ya, I just finished Fuedalism in school, and btw, if u make fun of me for my age, I'm sure everyone will agree that its only b/c u r just trying to find a factor to make me look worse for laying into you like you deserve, so leave that aside, thanks). Also, on raids, casters generally go in at 60-70% hp, not 20%, the complete opposite of 20%. Lag said shes probably gonna change this, b/c Haemish used the 60-70% rule, and guess what, he has 5 dragon heads on his walls from leading successful raids, so I&quot;m personally gonna side with him thanks very much.<br>
<br>
#3. Alright, about the bards in a healer group, here u do have some basis, some guilds/alliances use this style, however, its alot easier and faster for all concerned to die, which is what the vast majority of successful alliances/guilds do for these dragons. When you consider that healers generally are oom after the first rush, maybe about to 20% mana, well, they heal, not sure, healers let me know, but this seems very logical generally once every 6-8 seconds, possibly more, so medding between heals won't do a whole lot, which is why Lag said this is how its going to be and thats how it was.<br>
<br>
#4. This is my final topic, this one concerns raid discipline. Now, this time I&quot;m not taling about the run to the back of the lair discipline, that was a problem, but I'm talking about the unfaithful, selfish, undevoted, I won't listen to my leader b/c I know more than them discipline. To take it into your own hands and decide what you want to do and what not is completely unacceptable, and it is not allowed, and an insult to all of us out there who go out there and work our butts off. Now, you wanna talk about me? I kept going over and over, but u know what? dieing doesn't matter, u get rezed, no biggie, I was willing to do whatever it took to make this raid a success, and you know why we failed? b/c people thought that rules don't apply to them, and that they are too good and can do what they wish, u know what? this makes me SICK! You are no better than anyone else. Also, I&quot;m sure this post is pretty close to what lag and flar are thinking, I&quot;m not saying it is, but I&quot;m sure I are reading this nodding their heads, but b/c of their position, they can't make a post like this one, well, guess what, I CAN and WILL, because I'm completely disappointed in your conduct. You belittled and ridiculed Lagdalen's abilities, and she went out there and did this for you, and thats that thanks? Please, don't bother wasting the space on any more raids b/c I for one don't want to listen to you blame Lag and Flar, b/c we all see now who to really blame. I personally would rather see a person who had never done it before, u know why? they don't want to mess up, so they will do exactly as told, b/c they want to see the corpse of Lord Nagafen lying breathless on the ground more than anything, I know I did my first time, and I still do. Unfortunetly, some people just are too good to listen to instructions, huh? This is rediculous, and I feel I probably have the backing of everyone who truly wanted this raid to suceed, and BTW, thx for telling us ur reason for attending the upcoming Vox raid, I&quot;m sure Lag and Flar read that /slashed out your name on list of people, they shouldn't have to put on a show to ammuse your sorry *ss, thats rediculous, they deserve better respect, and u need to start showing it to them!<br>
<br>
